---
description: "Parallel lanes + ownership + wave-based integration"
alwaysApply: true
---

We run aggressive parallel execution. To prevent conflicts:

Lanes:
- W1: web pages/components (UI surface)
- W2: web composables/stores/services (logic)
- A1: api endpoints/controllers/routes
- A2: api domain/services/models
- T: tests
- I: deps/infra/CI/Docker
- D: DB migrations/schema

Ownership model: strict-by-default, soft-by-exception
- Stay within your lane file globs.
  - If you must touch outside, create artifacts/current/ownership-request.md and STOP until orchestrator approves.

Wave-based integration:
- Wave 0: shared contracts/types/config (serialized)
- Wave 1: backend A1/A2 parallel
- Wave 2: frontend W1/W2 parallel
- Wave 3: tests + hardening
